  "market_context": "ES (S&P 500 E-mini Futures) on 25 April 2024. During the London session (02:00–05:00 EST), price swept one side of a consolidation range, establishing a change in the state of delivery. The 8:30 AM news event then manipulated price higher before the true directional move lower unfolded.",
  "key_observation": "London swept the high of the range, creating a Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH). The 8:30 AM news spike manipulated price back up into London's order block (~5079–5083), providing a short entry. Price then delivered lower into the 9:30 and 10:00 AM important time levels.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the London session range on the ES 15-minute chart (25 April 2024) and observed that London swept the high side of the range.",
    "Step 2: Marked the series of up-close candles that were swept as the Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH), confirming a bearish bias.",
    "Step 3: Noted the prior swing low as the initial downside target once the CHoCH was confirmed.",
    "Step 4: Observed the 8:30 AM news event causing a manipulation spike higher, driving price back up into London's order block (approximately 5079–5083 area).",
    "Step 5: Identified London's order block as the short entry point following the 8:30 manipulation move.",
    "Step 6: Applied important time levels — 9:30 AM and 10:00 AM — as key reaction/target levels for the continuation lower.",
    "Step 7: Observed price moving lower into the 9:30 AM level, confirming the London Reversal daily profile with New York continuing in the direction established by London's liquidity sweep."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price moved lower after the 8:30 AM manipulation into London's order block, delivering into the 9:30 AM important time level as anticipated. The London Reversal profile played out with the daily candle forming an Open-High-Low-Close sequence.",
  "lessons": "In a London Reversal profile, London sweeps liquidity and creates a CHoCH. An 8:30 AM news spike can manipulate price back into London's order block, offering a high-probability short entry. The 9:30 and 10:00 AM time levels serve as key reaction and target zones for the continuation move.",
